result.execSummary:
The defendant Kim M. Pinnow-Johnson was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Theft-Business Setting >$10,000 [Modifiers: PTAC, as a Party to a Crime], a class G felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.20(1)(b).
  • Fraudulent Writings/By Corp. Officer [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.39(1).
  • Fraudulent Writings/By Corp. Officer [Modifiers: Party to a Crime], a class H felony, Wisconsin Statutes 943.39(1).

Charge(s) in this case were read in to this or other case(s). A "read in" charge is a charge that is dismissed as part of a plea agreement, however:

  • The defendant agrees to have the court consider the charge(s) when sentencing for another crime, under Wis. Stats. 973.20(1g)(b); and
  • The defendant cannot be prosecuted for these charge(s) in the future.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

Defendant Kim M. Pinnow-Johnson in court with attorney Michael J Steinle.  Kurt Brian Benkley appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  PSI addressed; changes and additions made.    Sentencing proceeded.  Statements by the State, defense and defendant.  Additional statements by:  Clark O.  Court found the state has satisfied victims' rights law.  Court ordered restitution in the amount of $104,877.84, joint and several, owed to Chubb Insurance Co.
Restitution to be collected by the Department of Corrections from 25% of funds under Sec. 973.05(4)(b), Wis. Stats.  Any balance due as a condition of ES; if not paid, a civil judgment to be entered.

COUNT 1:  
The Court sentenced the defendant to a TOTAL LENGTH of imprisonment of 4 years, concurrent with any other sentence.
The INITIAL TERM OF CONFINEMENT in the Wisconsin State Prisons is 2 years with credit for 38 days
time served.
The Court orders the defendant to serve a maximum term of EXTENDED SUPERVISION of 2 years.
Conditions of Extended Supervision to be determined by the Dept. of Corrections, but to include:  
*
*Alcohol and drug assessment and mental health assessment and comply with any treatment deemed necessary by the department.
*Maintain absolute sobriety.
*Random urine screens.  No positive results.
*No illegal drugs.
*No controlled substances without valid prescription.
*No contact with drug community.
*Seek and maintain full time employment.
*Cognitive Behavior Therapy.
*No contact with victim or co-actor.
- Defendant ordered to submit a DNA sample if not already done.
- Defendant advised that he/she may never again possess firearms or weapons.
- Civil rights suspended until reinstated.  Order received and filed.
- Pay all costs and surcharges, including the mandatory DNA surcharge, to be collected by the DOC out of up to 25% prison wages, any balance as a condition of ES.  If not paid, a civil judgment to be entered.
- Defendant does not qualify for the Challenge Incarceration Program but does qualify for the Wisconsin Substance Abuse Program after serving 1/2 initial confinement.
- Received and filed:  Written Explanation of Determinate Sentence; Notice of Right to Seek Postconviction Relief.
